But then:

1. developers can create new components in their render function. I guess, it's a sign that it's more flexible, so people can shoot themselves in the foot. Probably OK.
2. Developers can try to use hooks in render functions and have surprising behaviors. https://github.com/mui/mui-x/issues/4937#issuecomment-1132971135
1. for the developers who would read the source, it feels weird. With this pattern, I imagine that we can't really use JSX. I would read the source of Material UI a LOT when I was using it for a real project to customize it, to be honest, it was hard not to read the source, to truly use Material UI. Now, I think that the problem is mostly solved because Base UI is a separate package now. So I would continue to spend my time in the source of Material UI, and get clear sources to customize the styles, especially with the move to one React component for one DOM node.
